.TH "check_power_actors" 9 "check_power_actors" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
check_power_actors \- Check all cooling devices and warn when they are not power actors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" check_power_actors
.BI "(struct thermal_zone_device *tz "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tz" 12
thermal zone to operate on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Check all cooling devices in the \fItz\fP and warn every time they are missing
power actor API. The warning should help to investigate the issue, which
could be e.g. lack of Energy Model for a given device.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -EINVAL if any cooling device does not implement
the power actor API.
